# Simple Node Tooltip

Display tooltip for selected node in the Node Editor.

## Description

This Blender add-on allows you to display tooltips for selected nodes in the Node Editor. It adds a new option to the right-click menu in the Node Editor.

## Requirements

- Blender 2.93.0 or later

## Installation

1. Download the latest release of the add-on.
2. In Blender, go to Edit > Preferences > Add-ons.
3. Click on "Install..." and select the downloaded add-on file.
4. Enable the "Simple Node Tooltip" add-on by checking the checkbox.

## Usage

1. Open the Node Editor.
2. Right-click on a node to display its tooltip.

